# 專家權威可信度判斷方法：個人在挑選老師、線上課程、講者、教練時應該看哪些評估維度與決策依據

## 來源列表
1. [Know the Science: Finding Health Information Online — Is the Information Reviewed by Experts?](https://www.nccih.nih.gov/health/know-science/finding-and-evaluating-online-resources/finding-health-information-online/is-the-information-reviewed-by-experts) — Site Last Updated: 2026-04-30
2. [Know the Science: Finding Health Information Online — How Do You Know the Information Is Accurate?](https://www.nccih.nih.gov/health/know-science/finding-and-evaluating-online-resources/finding-health-information-online/how-do-you-know-the-information-is-accurate) — Site Last Updated: 2026-04-27
3. [How to Evaluate Trustworthiness in Science | NIH](https://www.nih.gov/about-nih/science-health-public-trust/perspectives/how-evaluate-trustworthiness-science) — Last reviewed: 2025-06-26
4. [What is the Credentialed Coach Finder? | ICF Support](https://icfsupport.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/5000881265-what-is-the-credentialed-coach-finder-ccf-) — Modified: 2026-02-16
5. [When a Business Offer or Coaching Program Is a Scam | FTC Consumer Advice](https://consumer.ftc.gov/articles/when-business-offer-or-coaching-program-scam) — 2022-08
6. [Vigilant trust in scientific expertise | European Journal for Philosophy of Science](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s13194-024-00619-z) — 2024-11-21
7. [Credibility Judgments in Higher Education | Education Sciences](https://www.mdpi.com/2227-7102/14/8/852) — 2024-08-07
8. [Investigate the Source — SIFT | Wayne State University Libraries](https://guides.lib.wayne.edu/sift/investigate) — Last updated: 2021-03-11

## 原文摘錄

### 來源 1
> “health experts reviewed it”

URL: https://www.nccih.nih.gov/health/know-science/finding-and-evaluating-online-resources/finding-health-information-online/is-the-information-reviewed-by-experts

### 來源 2
> “testimonials, anecdotes, unsupported claims, and opinions aren’t the same as objective, evidence-based information.”

URL: https://www.nccih.nih.gov/health/know-science/finding-and-evaluating-online-resources/finding-health-information-online/how-do-you-know-the-information-is-accurate

### 來源 3
> “Researchers in one field aren’t necessarily experts in related areas.”

URL: https://www.nih.gov/about-nih/science-health-public-trust/perspectives/how-evaluate-trustworthiness-science

### 來源 4
> “met specific training and experience requirements”

URL: https://icfsupport.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/5000881265-what-is-the-credentialed-coach-finder-ccf-

### 來源 5
> “Business coaching scammers often lie about their credentials.”

URL: https://consumer.ftc.gov/articles/when-business-offer-or-coaching-program-scam

### 來源 6
> “Not all forms of distrust are harmful.”

URL: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s13194-024-00619-z

### 來源 7
> “peer-reviewed or open-access journals and articles, government- or education-based websites, and industry professionals.”

URL: https://www.mdpi.com/2227-7102/14/8/852

### 來源 8
> “quick check into the expertise and agenda”

URL: https://guides.lib.wayne.edu/sift/investigate

## 關鍵重點

以下為我的整理說明：

- 看「是否有同領域專業資格」，不是只看名氣或跨領域頭銜。（對應來源 3）
- 看「資歷是否可驗證」，例如訓練時數、經驗要求、認證目錄、有效資格。（對應來源 4、5）
- 看「內容是否經專家審查」，尤其是健康、科學、投資、職涯等高風險主題。（對應來源 1）
- 看「是否提供證據」，並把研究、證據、意見、見證、成功故事分開判斷。（對應來源 2、7）
- 對「保證成果」「快速致富」「學生成功案例」保持懷疑，因為 FTC 明確把這類 coaching pitch 視為常見風險訊號。（對應來源 5）
- 使用 SIFT 的做法時，先查來源背後的人、機構、利益關係與議程，再投入內容本身。（對應來源 8）
- 對專家不是盲信，也不是全面不信；較好的態度是保留警覺、交叉查證、辨認偏誤與利益衝突。（對應來源 6）

## 不確定點

- 「老師、講者、線上課程、教練」橫跨教育、商業 coaching、健康、投資、職涯等領域，不同領域的正式資格制度差異很大。
- 教練領域未必都有強制執照；來源 5 指出 business coach 沒有 licensing requirement，因此只能依認證、經驗、學生回饋與第三方查證綜合判斷。
- 找到的近期資料多集中在 health/science information、business coaching scams、coach credential verification；「一般線上課程講師可信度」的官方近期指南較少。
